{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, there exists a distinct focus on physiological phenotyping in the field, and that is reflected in this review.",
    "These studies are critical to inform the necessary interventions that may improve hiPSC-CM functionality.",
    "This need places further emphasis on the importance of training data bias, for if bias exists in phenotyping methods, it may skew the results of interventions designed to these parameters.",
    "In addition, the training size itself is a crucial factor for almost every AI approach.",
    "Notably, the studies reviewed here rely on experimental data, particularly from cardiac differentiation experiments, as a primary data source."
  ]
}